If I boot verbose I see

  atrtc: atrtc-1 already exists; skipping it

This message comes from devclass_alloc_unit.

  printf("%s: %s%d already exists; skipping it\n", dc->name, dc->name, *unitp);

So *unitp == -1.  Variable

  int unit = *unitp;

was initialized to -1, or DEVICE_UNIT_ANY.  So this BUS_HINT_DEVICE_UNIT call must have happened.

	/* Ask the parent bus if it wants to wire this device. */
	if (unit == DEVICE_UNIT_ANY)
		BUS_HINT_DEVICE_UNIT(device_get_parent(dev), dev, dc->name,
		    &unit);

The printf is guarded by

	if (unit != DEVICE_UNIT_ANY)

so BUS_HINT_DEVICE_UNIT must have assigned a unit number.  This macro invokes
a bus_hint_device_unit method.  There are only three of these, one each for
isa, pci, and acpica.
